<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - December 2, 1996</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
December 2, 1996</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Watch out, the Politically Correct battalions are riding high
again.  They're back at the Smithsonian Institution.  This time,
they say they merely want to <I>update</I> some outmoded military
displays at the Museum of American History.

<p>

This is the same line we heard when they turned the fiftieth
anniversary of Hiroshima into an anti-American exhibit.  Last
year, the liberals' plans provoked a firestorm of protest from
veterans and their families.  In our schools, the Goals 2000 history
standards would have kids know about Madonna and the Simpsons,
but dropped Paul Revere, Albert Einstein and the U.S. landing
on the Moon.

<p>

The Smithsonian is a very popular tourist attraction in Washington.
That's because Americans know they can come here and see such
wonders as the flag that inspired <I>The Star-Spangled Banner</I>.
But the Smithsonian's politically correct staffers are often
ashamed of their nation's heritage.  They're unwilling to defend
it.  So we must honor our country's past.  And let's give thanks
to veterans and their patriotic supporters. They are keeping Paul
Revere's heritage alive.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

<center><b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwold.html.cgi#current">Last Month's Commentaries</a>] 
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwdaily.html.cgi#current">This Month's Commentaries</a>]
</b></center>

